verses.text_plain: Wine is a mocker, strong drink is raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.
verses.verse_html: 1Wine is a mocker, strong drink is raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.

verses.text_plain: The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion: whoso provoketh him to anger sinneth against his own soul.
verses.verse_html: 2The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion: whoso provoketh him to anger sinneth against his own soul.

verses.text_plain: It is an honour for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.
verses.verse_html: 3It is an honour for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.

verses.text_plain: The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold; therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing.
verses.verse_html:
4The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold; therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing. ▼
▼ cold: or, winter

verses.text_plain: Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.
verses.verse_html: 5Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.

verses.text_plain: Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?
verses.verse_html:
6Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find? ▼
▼ goodness: or, bounty

verses.text_plain: The just man walketh in his integrity: his children are blessed after him.
verses.verse_html: 7The just man walketh in his integrity: his children are blessed after him.

verses.text_plain: A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.
verses.verse_html: 8A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.

verses.text_plain: Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?
verses.verse_html: 9Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?

verses.text_plain: Divers weights, and divers measures, both of them are alike abomination to the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
10Divers weights, and divers measures, both of them are alike abomination to the Lord. ▼
▼ Divers weights: Heb. A stone and a stone
 , ▼
▼ divers measures: Heb. an ephah and an ephah

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Divers weights: Heb. A stone and a stone
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Divers weights: Heb. A stone and a stone

footnotes.body_text: ▼ divers measures: Heb. an ephah and an ephah
footnotes.body_html: ▼ divers measures: Heb. an ephah and an ephah

verses.text_plain: Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work be pure, and whether it be right.
verses.verse_html: 11Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work be pure, and whether it be right.

verses.text_plain: The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made even both of them.
verses.verse_html: 12The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made even both of them.

verses.text_plain: Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.
verses.verse_html: 13Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.

verses.text_plain: It is naught, it is naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.
verses.verse_html: 14It is naught, it is naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.

verses.text_plain: There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.
verses.verse_html: 15There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.

verses.text_plain: Take his garment that is surety for a stranger: and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.
verses.verse_html: 16Take his garment that is surety for a stranger: and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.

tokens.text: of him for a strange woman

verses.text_plain: Bread of deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.
verses.verse_html:
17Bread of deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel. ▼
▼ deceit: Heb. lying, or, falsehood

footnotes.body_html: ▼ deceit: Heb. lying, or, falsehood

verses.text_plain: Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.
verses.verse_html: 18Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.

verses.text_plain: He that goeth about as a talebearer revealeth secrets: therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips.
verses.verse_html:
19He that goeth about as a talebearer revealeth secrets: therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips. ▼
▼ flattereth: or, enticeth

verses.text_plain: Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness.
verses.verse_html:
20Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness. ▼
▼ lamp: or, candle

verses.text_plain: An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.
verses.verse_html: 21An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.

verses.text_plain: Say not thou, I will recompense evil; but wait on the Lord, and he shall save thee.
verses.verse_html: 22Say not thou, I will recompense evil; but wait on the Lord, and he shall save thee.

verses.text_plain: Divers weights are an abomination unto the Lord; and a false balance is not good.
verses.verse_html:
23Divers weights are an abomination unto the Lord; and a false balance is not good. ▼
▼ a false…: Heb. balance of deceit

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a false…: Heb. balance of deceit
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a false…: Heb. balance of deceit

verses.text_plain: Man’s goings are of the Lord; how can a man then understand his own way?
verses.verse_html: 24Man’s goings are of the Lord; how can a man then understand his own way?

verses.text_plain: It is a snare to the man who devoureth that which is holy, and after vows to make enquiry.
verses.verse_html: 25It is a snare to the man who devoureth that which is holy, and after vows to make enquiry.

verses.text_plain: A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.
verses.verse_html: 26A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.

verses.text_plain: The spirit of man is the candle of the Lord, searching all the inward parts of the belly.
verses.verse_html:
27The spirit of man is the candle of the Lord, searching all the inward parts of the belly. ▼
▼ candle: or, lamp

verses.text_plain: Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upholden by mercy.
verses.verse_html: 28Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upholden by mercy.

verses.text_plain: The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.
verses.verse_html: 29The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.

verses.text_plain: The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so do stripes the inward parts of the belly.
verses.verse_html:
30The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so do stripes the inward parts of the belly. ▼
▼ cleanseth…: Heb. is a purging medicine against

footnotes.body_text: ▼ cleanseth…: Heb. is a purging medicine against
footnotes.body_html: ▼ cleanseth…: Heb. is a purging medicine against
